In this study, PA interventions were defined as structured exercise programs designed to improve preschool children’s physical health through various forms of movement-based activities. Each intervention was categorized as “Physical Activity (PA)” to distinguish it from the “Control Group (CON)”, which consisted of children who did not participate in any structured exercise program.The dose of PA was quantified as the total weekly exercise time (minutes per week) [19], calculated using the following formula: PA Dose (min/week) = Duration per session (min) \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
